                <div class="col-sm-8">
                    <h5>THERESA BAGAN<span>- LEAD RMT - </span></h5>
                    <p class="text-justify">I have always had a strong connection to the holistic field. At a young age I was told my hands were strong and I should consider massage as a future career . In 1999 I took my first steps in that direction through a <em>Touch for Health</em> course. It opened my eyes to the healing possibilities of human touch and the power of our body’s response to touch. After I completed all 3 levels of Reiki through MRU, I was ready for massage school. I completed my 700hr program from <em>The Vancouver school of Bodywork and Massage</em>. This accelerated program offered me so much more than massage – Some other modalities I learned include <em>Joint Release, Aromatherapy, Ayurveda, Reflexology, Shiatsu, Deep Flow and Hot Stone Massage</em>. As a Holistic Massage practitioner, my intention is to help others experience the balance, vitality, strength and joy that comes from integrating the mind, body and spirit in a state of optimum health. My approach is to treat each individual with a customized treatment plan, combined with a desire to achieve the highest level of well-being. I aspire to deepen my understanding of the science of self-healing and the lifelong benefits that are associated with the commitment to one’s health. </p>
