                    <h5>SHAWNE KLASSEN<span>- RMT - </span></h5>
                    <p class="text-justify">“Pain is the body’s way of telling us that something is wrong…please pay attention.”</p>
                    <p class="text-justify">This calling into massage therapy has taken me on a tour of disciplines. Starting 20 years ago earning a massage diploma at Mount Royal College moving on to study accupressure, craniosacral therapy, Aquatic Therapy, Thai Massage and reflexology. Encompassing Each of my career path choices has helped shape my understanding of health and wellness. And, each choice has brought me into alignment with the strong, intuitive healer that I have always been. My current journey is to update my initial massage training with a 2200 hour orthopedic massage diploma hopefully finishing by the end of the summer.</p>
                    <p class="text-justify">My style of bodywork can integrate elements from several traditions, including Swedish, Thai, shiatsu, deep tissue, and myofascial release. The goal in our session is to find the right balance that will offer you therapeutic and restorative relaxation. That is the work; that is the journey.</p>
